This list hits way too close to home. The AI space is already littered with companies that prioritize convenience over consent, speed over substance, and profit over people. What's truly terrifying is how many of these “doomed” practices are being normalized in the name of innovation.

At Diedai, we've said no to every one of these. We don't play games with subscriptions, we don’t auto-connect payment methods, and we don’t hide behind bots when our users need help.

But the real danger isn’t just these practices — it’s the mindset that enables them. When you build for the lowest common denominator, you destroy the value you’re trying to create.

